 ihre Erweiterung um eine historische Perspektive. Als Fallbeispiel dienen drei Zeugnisse der deutschen Literatur- und Filmgeschichte: das mittelalterliche »Nibelungenlied«, Thea von Harbous Roman »Das Nibelungenbuch« (1923) und Fritz Langs zweiteiliger Film »Die Nibelungen« (1924).  aSociological research on intersectionality deals with the feature overlap of privilege and marginalization, including gender, class, race, nation, religion, sexuality, disability, and age. This volume has two innovative objectives: on the one hand, the development of intersectionality research for literary and cultural studies; on the other, its extension to a historical view. Two testimonies of the German »high culture« serve as a case study: the medieval Nibelungenlied and Fritz Lang's two-part film Die Nibelungen (1924).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aInterdisciplinary research. 0aSocial stratificationvCase studies. 4aAllgemeine Literaturwissenschaft. 4aFritz Lang. 4aGender Studies. 4aGender. 4aHelden. 4aIntersektionalität. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aLiteratur. 4aMittelalter. 4aMusikgeschichte. 4aNibelungen. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies.  aGender Studies.  aGender.  aGeneral Literature Studies.  aLiterature.  aMusic History.1 aBedekovic, Natasa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBedekovič, Nataša, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEzli, Lisa Pychlau-, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlinger, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrass, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKraß, Andreas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLembke, Astrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id